CREATE CUSTOMER FORM:
---------------------
URL: http://127.0.0.1:8000/customers/create
Method: GET (authenticated)

Fields:
- Name * (required, string, max 255)
- Email * (required, email validation, max 255)
- Phone (optional, string, max 50)
- Company Name (optional, string, max 255)
- Address (optional, textarea)

Validation:
✓ Required fields marked with red asterisk
✓ Email format validation
✓ Inline error messages on validation failure
✓ Form submission via Livewire (no page reload)

CUSTOMER DETAIL VIEW:
--------------------
URL: http://127.0.0.1:8000/customers/{id}
Method: GET (authenticated)

Displays:
- Customer information (name, email, phone, company, address)
- List of invoices for this customer with status badges
- List of quotations for this customer with status badges
- Edit Customer button
- Breadcrumb navigation (Customers / Customer Name)

Empty state handling:
✓ "No invoices yet" when customer has no invoices
✓ "No quotations yet" when customer has no quotations

EDIT CUSTOMER FORM:
-------------------
URL: http://127.0.0.1:8000/customers/{id}/edit
Method: GET (authenticated)

Features:
✓ Pre-populated form with existing customer data
✓ Same validation as create form
✓ "Update Customer" button text
✓ Success message after update
✓ Redirects to customer list after successful update

DELETE CUSTOMER:
----------------
Method: DELETE (via Livewire wire:click)
Confirmation: wire:confirm dialog shows "Are you sure you want to delete this customer?"
Action: Removes customer from database and refreshes list

